 351    public class AsyncUnityEventHandler : IUniTaskSource, IDisposable, IAsyncClickEventHandler
 352    {
 353        static Action<object> cancellationCallback = CancellationCallback;
 354
 355        readonly UnityAction action;
 356        readonly UnityEvent unityEvent;
 357
 358        CancellationToken cancellationToken;
 359        CancellationTokenRegistration registration;
 360        bool isDisposed;
 361        bool callOnce;
 362
 363        UniTaskCompletionSourceCore<AsyncUnit> core;
 364
 365        public AsyncUnityEventHandler(UnityEvent unityEvent, CancellationToken cancellationToken, bool callOnce)
 366        {
 367            if (cancellationToken.IsCancellationRequested)
 368            {
 369                isDisposed = true;
 370                return;
 371            }
 372
 373            this.action = Invoke;
 374            this.unityEvent = unityEvent;
 375            this.cancellationToken = cancellationToken;
 376            this.callOnce = callOnce;

 378            unityEvent.AddListener(action);

 380            if (cancellationToken.CanBeCanceled)

 382                registration = cancellationToken.RegisterWithoutCaptureExecutionContext(cancellationCallback, this);
 383            }

 386        }

 405        public void Dispose()
